# OpenAPI → service layer

When an OpenAPI spec under **`openapi/<slug>-api.*`** is added or changed, act as **@openapi-service-layer**:

1. Parse spec; infer **slug** from filename (`profile-api.json` → `profile`).
2. Map operations to service methods using **`operationId`** or verb rules (GET list → `list()`, GET `{id}` → `byId(id)`, GET single → `detail()`).
3. Write **`src/api/types/<featureDirName>.ts`** (wire-shape interfaces from schemas).
4. Write **`src/services/<featureDirName>Service.ts`** (object literal; **`get<T>()`** only — no axios).
5. Patch **`src/api/endpoints.ts`** and **`src/query/queryKeys.ts`** (replace feature block on regen).

**Do not** generate `network/`, `data/`, `viewmodels/`, Repositories, or ViewModels.

Screens use **`useAppQuery(QueryKeys…, () => service.method())`** — not generated OpenAPI clients.

Follow `.cursor/agents/openapi-service-layer.md`.

Write files directly; do not tell the user to run CLI unless blocked.
